An Ekiti State chief magistrate court sitting in Ado-Ekiti has ordered the remand of a 28-year-old man, Babatunde Olorunsola Ayomide, for allegedly raping a 14-year-old girl. The police prosecutor, Inspector Oriyomi Akinwale, told the court on Wednesday that Ayomide committed the offence on June 22, 2020 in Ado-Ekiti. Magistrate Adefunke Anoma, who frowned at the increasing rate of rape cases in the society, ordered that the defendant be remanded at the Nigeria Correctional Service, Ado-Ekiti, pending legal advice from the Ekiti State Director of Public Prosecution and adjourned the case till August 11, 2020 for mention. Man, 28, remanded for alleged rape Court remands man, 29, in prison for alleged rape of teenager Man, 50, remanded over alleged rape of minor